HEADWORD: Mucro
<hw>Mu"cro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>A minute abrupt point, as of a leaf; any
small, sharp point or process, terminating a larger part or
organ.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

